    <text id="B0410T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Johnson, of the Lincoln Temperance Association, sends Jackson information about
                    his group, at Jackson's request. Johnson asks that Jackson report on his
                    progress in formed local associations.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi> P. Jackson, <abbr
                            expan="Esquire">Esqr.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-08-30"><abbr expan="August">Aug</abbr> 30th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Washington City D.C.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>in compliance with your note bearing date 22nd ulti. I hasten to comply with your
                    request, and herewith send you twelve (12) copies of the plan and constitution
                    of Lincoln National Temperance Association, you will please inform me of the
                    success attendant on your exertions, and how many societies have been Organized
                    under its auspices, which will enable me to make my quarterly Report.</p>



                <closer>
                    <salute>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obed</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">Servt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi> Johnson<lb/>No 17 K Street<lb/><hi
                            rend="underline">Chairman <abbr expan="Executive Committee">Ex
                            Comt</abbr></hi></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
